one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T00:39:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK then.... you guys are weird.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNext Question?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cunjo Carl","CreatedById":162109,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T01:30:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf spaceX\u0027s new super alloy SX500 can handle 12000psi when superheated, can we finally use it to make a drilling machine to plunge through the Earth\u0027s crust?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T05:27:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut how to cool the tool?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T08:37:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527267\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548221259\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut how to cool the tool?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRegenerative coolant?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T08:57:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223526985\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548185044\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Green Baron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Green Baron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EReveal hidden contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Romans would of course use their cloaking device.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... err ... no ... wrong movie. Those were the Romulans ... nevermind.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBtw., the \u003Cs\u003ERomulan\u003C/s\u003E Roman Empire finally (phew) ended 1453 ;-) Renaissance is dawning ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell you have the holy roman empire.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot holy, roman or an empire as the joke went. Kind like\u00A0the democratic people republic meme\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T08:58:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527309\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548232645\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188222\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xd the great\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, Xd the great said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRegenerative coolant\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut where to drop the heat?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T09:48:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527317\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548233884\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n49 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut where to drop the heat?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou went the hot propelant, that is unless you can burn it in the engine.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T10:11:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProblems with deep drilling, besides the near impossibility to get the heat away, is pressure and keeping the borer from veering off. Kind of the opposite we want our contraptions to point :-) Boring deeper than a few km is really hard. The ocean crust has only ~8-10 km but temp gradient is high and one can as well dive to the middle ocean ridges or visit one of the ophiolites and have a direct look.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nContinental crust is something different, besides mechanical stress on a km-long borer, changing sedimentary and metamorphic stuff, the time needed, pressure and temp., the figures 12.000psi and 1200\u00B0C are a cool day in thin air once you\u0027re in the middle of the crust (let\u0027s say 30km). In some places where it is really thick and temp. gradient low it was tried before, but i think the deepest hole has 12km or so ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBesides that, i\u0027d expect other more dense materials than any steel alloy to be much more suited for such an enterprise. Requirements for a borer are rather different from that for a rocket ;-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-01-23T10:12:44Z\u0022 title=\u002201/23/2019 10:12  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 23, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Green Baron\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T10:18:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548238275\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Green Baron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Green Baron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn some\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E places where it is really thick and temp. gradient low it was tried before, but i think the deepest hole has 12km or so ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Kola hole stopped when it hit 180 \u00B0C in the Baltic Shield, approximately a third of the way to the mantle. A different project in Bavaria hit 260 \u00B0C merely at 9 km.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-01-23T10:18:45Z\u0022 title=\u002201/23/2019 10:18  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 23, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by DDE\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T10:50:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527339\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548238691\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n32 minutes ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Kola hole stopped when it hit 180 \u00B0C in the Baltic Shield, approximately a third of the way to the mantle. A different project in Bavaria hit 260 \u00B0C merely at 9 km.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep, conditions can be very different locally, much more than that actually.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are other sources than a drill core, cheaper to obtain, though more indirect.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-01-23T10:51:16Z\u0022 title=\u002201/23/2019 10:51  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 23, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Green Baron\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T11:25:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFunny.\u003Cbr\u003E\nHumans more or less see how to reach the stars and even can do this if really want.\u003Cbr\u003E\nBut I still haven\u0027t heard about any plausible idea how to reach the core just several thousand kilometers below.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey suggested to melt the way down with a big radioactive drop, but nothing about a working probe.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-01-23T11:27:11Z\u0022 title=\u002201/23/2019 11:27  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 23, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T12:26:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConditions are really hard down below, no material can stand this without being phase transformed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527349\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548242718\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey suggested to melt the way down with a big radioactive drop, but nothing about a working probe.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut what for ? There\u0027ll be a radioactive hole then and a warning sign (hopefully). Usually, such a project would aim to obtain some information, a drill core, temp./pressure readings, elemental phase transitions, exact position of boundary layers like the moho, etc. ... But we can get this information otherwise, just not with the accuracy of measured hole. What hasn\u0027t been replicated yet in a laboratory are the p/t conditions in the lower mantle and core. A pulsed machine can achieve this, but nothing that keeps the conditions long enough for minerals to form. So we actually do not know exactly what the material in the core is like.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep, it is easier to send a probe to the outer solar system than to obtain a sample from the earth\u0027s mantle, if not tectonic processes lift it up high enough.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-01-23T12:27:19Z\u0022 title=\u002201/23/2019 12:27  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 23, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Green Baron\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T12:31:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527359\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548246362\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Green Baron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Green Baron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut what for ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf there were a probe - to have a look,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"p1t1o","CreatedById":74091,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T20:18:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527349\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548242718\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFunny.\u003Cbr\u003E\nHumans more or less see how to reach the stars and even can do this if really want.\u003Cbr\u003E\nBut I still haven\u0027t heard about any plausible idea how to reach the core just several thousand kilometers below.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey suggested to melt the way down with a big radioactive drop, but nothing about a working probe.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it might be arguable that it should not be surprising that the core is a harder place to reach.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there more mass between a person on the Earth\u0027s surface and the core? Or between them and a nearish star?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-24T06:54:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527585\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548274736\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002274091\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022p1t1o\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, p1t1o said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there more mass between a person on the Earth\u0027s surface and the core? Or between them and a nearish star?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u002B1\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe first thing which came into my head when I had realized that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Wiki says, Alpha Centauri is\u00A0inside \u0022G-Cloud\u0022...\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alpha_Centauri#View_from_this_system\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alpha_Centauri#View_from_this_system\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. ... which is inside a \u0022Local Interstellar Cloud\u0022 (LIC), as well as we.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G-Cloud\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G-Cloud\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAlthough it\u0027s not clear if we are inside the G-Cloud, too., but both of us are definitely inside LIC, and G anyway occupies almost everything between us, we are right near it\u0027s wall.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022220px-The_Local_Interstellar_Cloud_and_n\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022228\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/The_Local_Interstellar_Cloud_and_neighboring_G-cloud_complex.gif/220px-The_Local_Interstellar_Cloud_and_neighboring_G-cloud_complex.gif\u0022 width=\u0022220\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3 And LIC is 30 ly wide.\u003Cbr\u003E\nWe have enetered it 40..150 ky ago (look! when the humans became clever!) and will leave it 10..20 ky later.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022220px-Local_Interstellar_Clouds_with_mot\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022220\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Local_Interstellar_Clouds_with_motion_arrows.jpg/220px-Local_Interstellar_Clouds_with_motion_arrows.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022220\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd it\u0027s hot. As hot as Sun, 7000 K. We live in oven,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EThe cloud has a temperature of about 7,000\u00A0K (6,730\u00A0\u00B0C; 12,140\u00A0\u00B0F),\u003C/span\u003E\u003Csup style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:11.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_Interstellar_Cloud#cite_note-near-earth-4\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0b0080;\u0022\u003E[4]\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eabout the same temperature as the surface of the Sun. However, its\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Specific_heat_capacity\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0b0080;font-size:14px;\u0022 title=\u0022Specific heat capacity\u0022\u003Especific heat capacity\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eis very low because it is not very dense, with 0.3 atoms per cubic centimetre (4.9/cu\u00A0in). This is less dense than the average for the interstellar medium in the\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milky_Way\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0b0080;font-size:14px;\u0022 title=\u0022Milky Way\u0022\u003EMilky Way\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E(0.5/cm\u003C/span\u003E\u003Csup style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:11.2px;\u0022\u003E3\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eor 8.2/cu\u00A0in), though six times denser than the gas in the hot, low-density Local Bubble (0.05/cm\u003C/span\u003E\u003Csup style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:11.2px;\u0022\u003E3\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eor 0.82/cu\u00A0in) which surrounds the local cloud.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Csup style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:11.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_Interstellar_Cloud#cite_note-JPL_interstellar-3\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0b0080;\u0022\u003E[3]\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Csup style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:11.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_Interstellar_Cloud#cite_note-Boulanger-5\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0b0080;\u0022\u003E[5]\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003EIn comparison,\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atmosphere_of_Earth\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0b0080;font-size:14px;\u0022 title=\u0022Atmosphere of Earth\u0022\u003EEarth\u0027s atmosphere\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eat\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K%C3%A1rm%C3%A1n_line\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0b0080;font-size:14px;\u0022 title=\u0022K\u00E1rm\u00E1n line\u0022\u003Ethe edge of space\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Ehas around 1.2\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u00D7\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E10\u003C/span\u003E\u003Csup style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:11.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E13\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Emolecules per cubic centimeter, dropping to around 50 million (5.0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u00D7\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E10\u003C/span\u003E\u003Csup style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:11.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E7\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E) at 450\u00A0km (280\u00A0mi).\u003C/span\u003E\u003Csup style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:11.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_Interstellar_Cloud#cite_note-6\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0b0080;\u0022\u003E[6]\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, we can take 0.3 atoms (probably, H) per cm\u003Csup\u003E3\u003C/sup\u003E. = 3*10\u003Csup\u003E5\u003C/sup\u003E at./m\u003Csup\u003E3\u003C/sup\u003E\u00A0= 3*10\u003Csup\u003E5\u003C/sup\u003E * 1*10\u003Csup\u003E-3\u003C/sup\u003E / 6.022*10\u003Csup\u003E23\u003C/sup\u003E\u00A0~= 5*10\u003Csup\u003E-22\u003C/sup\u003E kg/m\u003Csup\u003E3\u003C/sup\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndensity * distance:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEarth ~= 3000 km * 3000 kg/m3 = 3*10\u003Csup\u003E6\u003C/sup\u003E * 3000 ~= 1*10\u003Csup\u003E10\u003C/sup\u003E kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo aCen ~= 4.3 * 9.5*10\u003Csup\u003E15\u003C/sup\u003E * 5*10\u003Csup\u003E-22\u003C/sup\u003E ~=2*10\u003Csup\u003E-5\u003C/sup\u003E kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, it\u0027s 5*10\u003Csup\u003E14\u003C/sup\u003E times more matter between us and the Earth core than between us and closest stars.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA funny thing: the Sun surface, the Earth core, the gas cloud around us are ~6500..7000 K hot.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd we are between them and so cool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUpd.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI haven\u0027t counted the gas inside the Solar system itself, so maybe not 5*10\u003Csup\u003E14\u003C/sup\u003E times, but just 10\u003Csup\u003E14\u003C/sup\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-01-24T08:30:57Z\u0022 title=\u002201/24/2019 08:30  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 24, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-24T08:27:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527854\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548312856\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u002B1\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe first thing which came into my head when I had realized that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Wiki says, Alpha Centauri is\u00A0inside \u0022G-Cloud\u0022...\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alpha_Centauri#View_from_this_system\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alpha_Centauri#View_from_this_system\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. ... which is inside a \u0022Local Interstellar Cloud\u0022 (LIC), as well as we.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G-Cloud\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G-Cloud\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAlthough it\u0027s not clear if we are inside the G-Cloud, too., but both of us are definitely inside LIC, and G anyway occupies almost everything between us, we are right near it\u0027s wall\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E.\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAmusingly, the two clouds are inside a low-density Local Bubble, so the LIC is below average Milky Way density.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"p1t1o","CreatedById":74091,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-24T20:20:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527854\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548312856\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI haven\u0027t counted the gas inside the Solar system itself, so maybe not 5*10\u003Csup\u003E14\u003C/sup\u003E times, but just 10\u003Csup\u003E14\u003C/sup\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow I wasnt expecting such a big difference!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-24T20:53:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is actually even worse, earth\u0027s crustal density is ~2.7 (continental) to ~3.0 (oceanic), mantle density increasing to ~5.8 with depth. Then a juicy discontinuity at the core/mantle boundary to ~10, increasing to just below 13 in the inner core. Since the mantle makes by far for the most volume, it is safe to assume a medium density of 4 or even 4.5 for the calculation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-01-24T20:56:45Z\u0022 title=\u002201/24/2019 08:56  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 24, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Green Baron\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-09T08:29:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat if we are an experiment of an alien race to understand the development of life forms?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-09T08:35:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223537604\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549700950\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188222\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xd the great\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Xd the great said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat if we are an experiment of an alien race to understand the development of life forms?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey failed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-09T09:37:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223537604\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549700950\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188222\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xd the great\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Xd the great said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat if we are an experiment of an alien race to understand the development of life forms?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u2019s the same epitome of solipsism as the Simulation Theory, where the absense of evodemce is justified by raising the bar for the other side\u2019s evidence-hiding ability.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe two are ultimate conspiracy theories.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-09T09:46:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf we are a simulation, somewhere should be a readable debug log...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}